The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Pak players set for pay cut
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Pak players set for pay cut
                      
	Karachi: Pakistan cricketers are a concerned lot these days with reports claiming that the board is set to revise their central contracts which might result in salary cuts.         
	Sources in the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) said that a proposal to revise the central contracts  its terms and a reduction in monetary benefits for the players  was under consideration but nothing was final as yet.         
	The board is going through a difficult time because earnings have dried up this year due to the teams refusing to tour Pakistan because of security reasons. Second, the previous board wasted a lot of money which is being looked into, one source said.         
	He said the board had now embarked on a drive to cutexpenditure and reduce staff strength to balance its financial position . (PTI)                                                                                                                          
